messages.message:
Patch Set 5: Code-Review+1

> I agree that this can be done, I didn't do that just because there
 > is no use cases for trying bits on client now. If you have some
 > idea about that, please add comment in the ticket. I am OK to
 > continue with the new patch about client side trybits, but I'd land
 > this one first.

fair enough, in that case, I would suggest you to revise ldlm_inodebits as:

  struct ldlm_inodebits {
     __u64 bits;
     __u64 try_bits;
 }

and remove the current definition of 'struct ldlm_inodebits_wire' because it's known that this data structure is going to be changed.
